TASK-1-PRESENTATION REPORT
I created my digital literacy infographic using Canva, where I selected a fun and interactive template that already included relevant images and design elements. Instead of designing everything from scratch, I focused on customizing the content and arranging the sections in a clear and visually appealing way. Canva’s drag-and-drop features and built-in icons made the process easier and more interesting.
The infographic covers key aspects of digital literacy such as understanding digital tools, practicing safe internet usage, and being responsible online. I included tools like Canva for designing and GitHub for project work and version control. Using visuals and icons helped me present the information in a more engaging way instead of just plain text.
One challenge I faced was attaching the infographic image in VS Code and uploading it to GitHub. It was confusing at first, especially understanding file paths, but after some effort, I was able to figure it out. Overall, this task was both creative and technical, and it helped me learn useful skills for the future.
